<div id="review_3928378819" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3928378819" />
    <a title="Otis Williams" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/88985113-otis-williams"><img alt="Otis Williams" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607957228p2/88985113.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3928378819?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Otis Williams" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Otis Williams" href="/user/show/88985113-otis-williams">Otis Williams</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3928378819" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7330585427110140014">Reform or Revolution (RoR) is, without a doubt, one of the most prevalent books that exist today. Luxemburg concisely, concretely, and logically lays down the argument that reform is a means to an end, not the end itself. She saw a growing streak in the German Socal Democratic Party (SPD) of opportunism and revisionism culminating in Evolutionary Socialism by Eddard Bernstein. Through ROR she astounding lays out the reasons Bernstein is wrong in every possible way and why reform can be used but </span>
  <span id="freeText7330585427110140014" style="display:none">Reform or Revolution (RoR) is, without a doubt, one of the most prevalent books that exist today. Luxemburg concisely, concretely, and logically lays down the argument that reform is a means to an end, not the end itself. She saw a growing streak in the German Socal Democratic Party (SPD) of opportunism and revisionism culminating in Evolutionary Socialism by Eddard Bernstein. Through ROR she astounding lays out the reasons Bernstein is wrong in every possible way and why reform can be used but is not the *only* use of the Proletariat. <br /><br />I absolutely recommend this to anyone and everyone. Especially anyone who still has any faith in the Bourgeoisie system that is the United States. Electoralism is viewed as the end all be all in modern revisionist discourse (i.e Liberals and “leftists” who believe in “Blue no matter who”) and it is a discourse that is proven to get us nowhere. It is a disturbing but entirely accurate thought that post-WWI Germany is an excellent depiction of the modern United States. And we all know what happened not long after this period in German History.<br /><br />This is an exceptionally easy read and lays out quite a few advanced topics in a very digestible format. It is an absolute shame Rosa was murdered by the Freikorps (the right-wing paramilitary squad) ordered by the SPD (because when you scratch a liberal a fascist bleeds) Gone much too soon and I believe without a doubt history would have gone differently had this tragic event not occurred. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7330585427110140014" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


