      var newTip = new Tip($('bookCover_925082'), "\n\n  <h2><a class=\"readable bookTitle\" href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/925082.Wage_Labour_and_Capital_Value_Price_and_Profit?from_choice=false&amp;from_home_module=false\">Wage-Labour and Capital/Value, Price and Profit<\/a><\/h2>\n\n      <div>\n        by <a class=\"authorName\" href=\"/author/show/7084.Karl_Marx?a=9&amp;origin=related_works\">Karl Marx<\/a>\n      <\/div>\n\n          <div class=\"smallText uitext darkGreyText\">\n            <span class=\"minirating\"><span class=\"stars staticStars notranslate\"><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p3\"><\/span><\/span> 4.30 avg rating &mdash; 1,605 ratings<\/span>            &mdash; published 1849\n          <\/div>\n\n    <div class=\"addBookTipDescription\">\n      \n<span id=\"freeTextContainer14373753471503011841\">The text of &quot;Wage-Labour and Capital&quot; came from lectures Marx delivered to the German Workmen&apos;s Club of Brussels in 1847, a time of great political upheaval. The relation between wage-labour to capital is a core concept in Marx&apos;s analysis of politica<\/span>\n  <span id=\"freeText14373753471503011841\" style=\"display:none\">The text of &quot;Wage-Labour and Capital&quot; came from lectures Marx delivered to the German Workmen\'s Club of Brussels in 1847, a time of great political upheaval. The relation between wage-labour to capital is a core concept in Marx\'s analysis of political economy. This book is an essential, a foundation to understanding the development of Marxist theory. &quot;Price. Value and Profit&quot; was written in 1865. The different parts, as in the title decomposes into \'surplus value\' (the essential economic building block in Marism). This book, again, is basic to understan